From 6117caa661a8b1bb757c15e5e2e7c6bd40c34fbb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 18:08:51 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Use external library dependencies

This changes the dependencies on the following libraries so
that they are provided at build time instead of being
fetched, built, and installed by CMake:

 - boost_mp11
 - Microsoft.GSL
 - ONNX
 - date
 - flatbuffers
 - CCCL

cutlass is intentionally NOT in this list. ORT 1.24.2's
cmake/external/cutlass.cmake uses the standalone
'FetchContent_Populate(cutlass)' form (the deprecated form) which
does NOT honor 'FIND_PACKAGE_ARGS' or
'FETCHCONTENT_TRY_FIND_PACKAGE_MODE=ALWAYS'; only
'FetchContent_MakeAvailable' does. So adding 'FIND_PACKAGE_ARGS'
to ORT's cutlass.cmake would be a no-op. We keep the in-layer
'recipes-devtools/cutlass/cutlass_<X.Y.Z>.bb' recipe pinned to the
SAME version that ORT's cmake/deps.txt declares (currently 4.2.1)
so the in-sysroot install of 'examples/41_fused_multi_head_attention/*'
matches the FetchContent-populated '_deps/cutlass-src/examples/...'
that ORT builds against (kernel_forward.h includes those headers
via '#include "41_fused_multi_head_attention/..."', and version
mismatch between sysroot and _deps yields hard-to-debug template
instantiation errors during nvcc compile of fmha_sm*.cu).

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [OE-specific]
Signed-off-by: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
Made-with: Cursor
